{"id":"math240-laplace_poly240-002","cid":"MATH 240","topic":"Laplace Transforms","subtopic":"Laplace transform of power functions","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A forcing function is f(t) = {a}*t^{n}. Find the Laplace transform F(s) and identify the numerator coefficient.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":4},"n":{"type":"int","min":1,"max":3}},"answer_expr":"laplace_poly240","steps":["L[{a}*t^{n}] = {a}*{n}! / s^{exp_p1}.","Numerator: {a}*{nfact} = {coeff}.","F(s) = {answer_laplace_poly240}/s^{exp_p1}."],"tags":["ode","Laplace","transform","forcing"]}
